### 9. Remove dead training commands and mock training infrastructure

**Problem:** Investigation confirmed all training functionality is dead code тАФ no ML backend exists anywhere in the codebase. The commands are stubs that call non-existent endpoints or return hardcoded responses.

**What's dead:**

| Command/Component | Status | Evidence |
|---|---|---|
| `aitbc hermes status` | Calls non-existent endpoint | `/v1/hermes/status` not in production (mock-only, `enable_mock_hermes=False`) |
| `aitbc hermes stop` | Calls non-existent endpoint | `POST /v1/hermes/agents/{id}/stop` doesn't exist anywhere |
| `aitbc hermes train` | Stub тАФ runs CLI via subprocess | No ML training, just logs to `/var/log/aitbc/agent-training/` |
| `aitbc hermes-training train` | Hardcoded stub | Returns `{"status": "training_started"}` |
| `aitbc hermes-training status` | Hardcoded stub | Returns `{"status": "in_progress", "progress": 45, "loss": 0.234}` |
| `coordinator-api/routers/training.py` | Mock-only router | Disabled in production (`enable_mock_training=False`) |
| `coordinator-api/services/training_service.py` | In-memory state only | No ML framework, no training backend |
| `coordinator-api/routers/hermes.py` mock endpoints | Mock-only | `POST /agents/{id}/status` returns `{"success": True}` |

**Fix:** Delete all training commands and mock training infrastructure.

**Files deleted:**
- `cli/aitbc_cli/commands/hermes_training.py` тАФ 100% hardcoded stubs
- `apps/coordinator-api/src/app/routers/training.py` тАФ mock-only router
- `apps/coordinator-api/src/app/services/training_service.py` тАФ in-memory state, no ML
- `cli/tests/test_commands_hermes_training.py` тАФ tests for deleted stubs

**Files updated (remove training commands):**
- `cli/aitbc_cli/commands/hermes.py` тЖТ `agent.py` тАФ remove `status`, `stop`, and `train` commands; keep `ping`, `request-coins`, `send`, `receive`, `peers`, `agent` (message)
- `cli/aitbc_cli/core/main.py` тАФ remove `hermes_training` import and registration
- `cli/aitbc_cli/config.py` тАФ remove `coordinator_url` (deprecated 8203, only used by status/stop)
- `apps/coordinator-api/src/app/main.py` тАФ remove training router include
- `apps/coordinator-api/src/app/config.py` тАФ remove `enable_mock_training` and `enable_mock_hermes` fields
- `apps/coordinator-api/src/app/routers/__init__.py` тАФ remove training router import
- `cli/README.md`, `cli/CLI_USAGE_GUIDE.md` тАФ remove training command references
- `cli/docs/DISABLED_COMMANDS_CLEANUP.md` тАФ remove training references
- `skills/aitbc/aitbc-cli.md` тАФ remove "Agent Training Operations" section
- `skills/hermes-autonomy-testing/` тЖТ `skills/agent-autonomy-testing/` тАФ remove training endpoint references

**Note:** The `hermes train` command (lines 123-235 of `hermes.py`) is the largest stub тАФ it parses a JSON training-data file, executes operations via `subprocess.run(["hermes", "agent", ...])`, and logs results. It doesn't connect to any ML backend. Removing it is safe тАФ no production workflow depends on it.

**Tests:**
- `aitbc agent train --help` should fail (command removed)
- `aitbc agent status --help` should fail (command removed)
- `aitbc agent stop --help` should fail (command removed)
- `aitbc agent-training --help` should fail (module deleted)
- Remaining `agent` commands (`ping`, `request-coins`, `send`, `receive`, `peers`) still work

